# IBM HR Analytics â€“ Employee Attrition Analysis

## Overview
This project analyses employee attrition using the IBM HR Analytics dataset. 
The analysis was conducted entirely in Excel, focusing on data cleaning, pivot tables, and visualisation to identify key drivers of employee attrition.

## Tools Used
- Microsoft Excel
- Pivot Tables
- Excel Charts & Visualisations

## Dataset
The dataset is the IBM HR Analytics Employee Attrition dataset, containing employee demographic, job role, performance, income, and satisfaction data.

## Data Cleaning
The following steps were performed in Excel:
- Checked for missing or inconsistent values
- Standardised column formatting
- Removed unnecessary fields
- Created calculated columns where required
- Ensured data types were correct for analysis

## Analysis Performed
Pivot tables and charts were used to analyse:
- Attrition by department
- Attrition by job role
- Attrition by age group
- Attrition by salary band
- Attrition vs years at company

## Key Insights
- Higher attrition observed in specific job roles and departments
- Early-career employees had higher turnover compared to long-tenured staff

